    "They range from basic theories on the action of wind energy conversion systems to the practical control methods employed.",
    "The control system overview in DFIGs reported by Cardenas et al. (2013) has been cited more frequently, suggesting it has a research basis in wind energy applications.",
    "In a similar vein, Kelkoul et al. (2021) deals with an objective comparison of Classical Sliding Mode Control (SMC) and Super Twisting Algorithm (STA), the implementation of which in wind variable conditions is considered to be the best practices of modern approaches that improve the stability of the system.",
    "Xu's papers (2006, 2007) are well-known for their contribution to the investigation of dynamic modeling and direct power control of DFIGs, power improvement in the presence of unbalanced grid voltage.",
    "Altogether these works have significantly contributed to the current research on grid connected wind energy systems."
